{ This is not the main line, but - after examining the other possible lines and responses for Black as suggested by - amongst others - Kannappan in his book regarding the Modernized Berlin Wall, it's White's best attempt in the quest for an advantage. }
12... g6 13. h3
{ This is the style of playing I adhere and recommend: slowly building up the pressure maintaining the cohesion between the pieces.  I couldn't find any advantage for White after  13.d5  Nb8  14.b3  c6  15.c4  Qc7  16.Ne3  Nbd7  17.Ba3  Rb8  18.dxc6  Qxc6  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@43@@EndBracket@@ Carlsen, M @@StartBracket@@2675@@EndBracket@@-Svidler, P @@StartBracket@@2742@@EndBracket@@ Longyearbyen 2006. }
