13. exd5 Qxd5 14. Ne3 Qd8
{ Probably the best, however it strikes me that such a passive move is an ill omen. }
15. Ng4
{ An artificial placement of the knight, though not without effect. Hitting the central point on e5 and unpinning, and this, paving the way for d3-d4. }
15... Nd7 16. d4
{ The time is ripe for such an energetic move in the center, due to White's strong pieces. }
16... exd4 17. Nxd4
{ The idea of reaching a close to a symmetrical pawn structure, is that White wants to exploit his better piece activity. }
17... Nxd4 18. Qxd4
{ Another illustrative line to illustrate in what pickle Black is. } 18... Nf6
19. Nxf6+ Bxf6 20. Qxd8
{ Suddenly, we get the possibility to trap the bishop. } 20... Raxd8
{ Of course, Bxd8 should have been preferred. But after this passive move it is evident who is in charge. }
21. g4 Bg6 22. Bxg6 hxg6 23. g5 { Black loses a piece. } *

