9... d5 10. Nbd2 dxe4 11. dxe4
{ Black's three main options here are: @@StartBracket@@1@@EndBracket@@  11...Be6  , @@StartBracket@@2@@EndBracket@@  11...Bd6  and @@StartBracket@@3@@EndBracket@@  11...Bc5  .    Before we delve into these theoretical and interesting positions, I would like to stress that there is not such a thing as an 'antidote' against these positions.  However, based on some strong ideas of the current leading players, we can get a grasp of the strategies involved and turn on the heat on our opponent maximally. }
11... Be6 12. a4
{ This is the soft spot of Black's position. Our plan is to engage on this target by means of Qe2 and evt. Bd3. }
12... b4 13. Qe2 { Developing and preparing Nc4. } 13... Qc8 14. Nc4
{ Black has to protect his pawn on e5. } 14... Nd7 15. a5
{ Though this is a balanced position, it occurs to me that White is a bit better here. Black is suffering from a lack of space since his knights have to defend the pawn on e5.  After White's last move, he took away the b6-square from the d7-knight whereas Black has to anticipate on Ba4. By contrast, White has plenty of space to manoeuvre. }
15... f6
{ The e5-pawn got his extra protection, but now the d5- and f5-square become more vulnerable. }
16. Ne3
{ White's strategy seems to pay out. Black is cramped and there are several threats to avert, beginning with Ba4 or Nd5. }
16... b3 17. Bd3
{ This is even stronger than the continuation in the game. We are tight on target by aiming to trade off the best piece and main guardian of our opponent: the black light-squared bishop.   17.Bb1  Also here White got the better position. Let yourself be inspired by this pearl of a game played by the elegant Slovakian GM Sergei Movsesian. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@49@@EndBracket@@ Movsesian, S @@StartBracket@@2698@@EndBracket@@-Almasi, Z @@StartBracket@@2713@@EndBracket@@ Istanbul 2012. }
17... Nc5 18. Bc4 { Obtaining full control over the light squares. } 18... Kh8
19. Bd5
{ The knight can't be moved and taking on d5 would help White's piece play considerably. }
