{ Here again, Black has a choice. He can continue with  11...h6  or  11...Bb7  .   There are so many possible ways to go here. Let's give you another popular line.  11.d4  Bb7   11...exd4  12.cxd4  Bg4  13.Nf1  g6  14.Ng3  1-0 @@StartBracket@@40@@EndBracket@@ Nepomniachtchi, I @@StartBracket@@2784@@EndBracket@@ - Carlsen, M @@StartBracket@@2862@@EndBracket@@ chess24.com INT 2020.  12.a4  Nb8  13.Bd3  c6  14.b3  when we get a typical Breyer position with chances for both sides. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@48@@EndBracket@@ Svidler, P  @@StartBracket@@2723@@EndBracket@@ - Carlsen, M @@StartBracket@@2863@@EndBracket@@ chess24.com INT 2020. }
11... g6 12. d4
{ 12.d4  is rarely played, but not necessarily weaker than the more frequently seen  12.a4  .   For example  12.a4!?  Bb7  13.Bg5  h6  14.Bh4  Bg7  15.Ne3  Qd7  16.b4  Ne7   16...Nd8!  17.Nd2  Ne6⇆  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@61@@EndBracket@@ Fressinet, L @@StartBracket@@2711@@EndBracket@@ - Amin, B @@StartBracket@@2628@@EndBracket@@ Saint Quentin 2014.  17.Bb3  Nh5⇆  1-0 @@StartBracket@@26@@EndBracket@@ Carlsen, M @@StartBracket@@2847@@EndBracket@@ -Yip, C @@StartBracket@@2430@@EndBracket@@ chess24.com INT 2021. }
12... Bg7 { 12...h6  transposes to the 11...h6 12.d4! g6 variation. } 13. d5
{ In these closed positions, slightly resembling the King's Indian Defense, the rook seems somewhat misplaced on e8. }
13... Ne7 14. a4 { Playing on two flanks.. } 14... Bd7 15. Ng3
{ Deploying the c-pawn to hit the center, would have the disadvantage that the a2-g8 diagonal will be opened. }
15... c6 16. dxc6 Bxc6 17. axb5
{ Given the fact that the bishop should take back on a8, Black will need time to reorganize his pieces. }
17... axb5 18. Rxa8
{ Black cannot take back with the queen, since the d6-pawn would be hanging. }
18... Bxa8 19. h4
{ This new idea, seen throughout these chapters, causes Black sleepless nights. }
19... Bc6 20. h5
{ The point behind the aggressive pawn march is that Black can hardly encounter White's @@StartBracket@@Bb3 followed by@@EndBracket@@ Ng5 since h7-h6 leads to a serious weakening of the king after hxg6. }
20... Qc7 21. Bb3
{ It appears that Black's knight on e7 is misplaced. White has many attacking ideas @@StartBracket@@Bg5 or Ng5/Nh4 followed by Qf3, possibly with h5-h6 included too@@EndBracket@@ without risking anything. }
