11... h6 12. d4
{ This is not the main line, but - after examining the other possible lines and responses for Black as suggested by - amongst others - Kannappan in his book regarding the Modernized Berlin Wall, it's White's best attempt in the quest for an advantage. }
12... Bg4
{ Black is using the fact that White has not @@StartBracket@@yet@@EndBracket@@ played h3. However, as we see in the following moves, White can use this fact to his advantage too. }
13. Ng3
{ Allowing a doubled pawn on f3, but counting on the arising attacking chances along the g-file. }
13... exd4 14. cxd4 Bxf3 15. gxf3 { is a transposition to the main line. }
15... Nb4
{ Black's idea of Nb4 and c5 is common - as well in the Ragozin line of the Ruy Lopez. }
