19. a4 bxa4 20. Rxa4 Nb4
{ We are stuck with a doubled f-pawn and we know that Black will - in any case - endeavor to play g6, Bg7, and possibly h5-h4, and Nh5. Let's turn our weakness into a strength - let's turn water into wine! }
21. Kh1 { This first prophylactic move in a sequence. } 21... g6 22. f4
{ White is now well enough prepared for the advance. } 22... h5
{ will not bring Black any luck, as after } 23. Rg1 h4
{ It's not mandatory to retreat. } 24. Nh5 Nxh5 25. Qxh5
{ White wants to open the g-file now with f5. } 25... Bg7 26. Qg4
{ White obtained a closely to winning position. Black can't be saved after the sadistically slow but striking Ra4-a3-h3. }
