Qd3 { Black should react to the threat of e5 and Qh7. } 22... g6
{ Undoubtedly, Black should play this as his f8-bishop cannot stay passive for the rest of the game. But it contains a deficiency. }
23. Bd2
{ A key plan to remember. After g6, the dark squares have become vulnerable. For this reason, White immediately plays his bishop to the long diagonal. }
23... Qc7 24. Bc3
{ White is much better here. After  24...Bg7  25.Bxg7  Kxg7  the black king is on its own. Things could go awry for Black.  26.Qc3+  It becomes manifest that the king is not sufficiently protected.  26...Kh7  27.Nh2!  Bd7  28.f4  White obtained a large advantage. }
