{ We grab the opponent by the throat as he is not yet unpinned, and he cannot take on d4 because of e5.   Recently, Firouzja played the following line and won, but the acquired position out of the opening was double-edged:   9.Nbd2  Black can now smoothly start his attacking operations, while not having to care about any tension in the center:  9...g5  10.Bg3  Nd7  We should get acquainted with Black's knight manoeuvre by now.  11.d4  Qf6!  Fortifying e5 and preparing to hide the king to a safer place.  12.Re1  O-O-O  1-0 @@StartBracket@@36@@EndBracket@@ Firouzja, A @@StartBracket@@2723@@EndBracket@@-Le, Q @@StartBracket@@2713@@EndBracket@@ Moscow 2019. }
9... g5 10. dxe5
{ The best continuation, as our e4-pawn is hanging @@StartBracket@@as well@@EndBracket@@. }
10... gxh4 11. exd6
{ It turns out that after a lot of exchanges our pawn structure is to be preferred. }
11... cxd6 12. Nc3
{ Completing the development, while we counter  12...Nh5  with  13.Nd4  Nf4  and  14.Nce2! }
12... h3 13. Qd4
{ The queen occupies the perfect spot. From here, it keeps an eye on the entire board. }
13... c5
{ In case our opponent still wants to castle, he should repel the Qxa7 threat.   Please note that  13...Qe7  14.Rfe1  Rg8   14...hxg2  15.Rad1  Now Black cannot castle long, as a7 is hanging.  15.g3  leaves Black nowhere. }
14. Qd2
{ The subtle point of our play is that we let Black take on g2: it entails the closing of the g-file. }
14... Qe7 15. Rad1
{ Again we don't take back the pawn on g2 once Black takes. } 15... O-O-O 16.
Rfe1
{ Plain and simple. We can play natural moves as our pawn structure is much better. }
16... Bg4
{ After taking on g2, we got rid of concerns about an enemy's kingside attack.  16...hxg2  17.Nb5!  Kb8  18.Nxd6±  following up with Qf4 or e4-e5. }
17. Qe3
{ The queen defends the third rank. White is aiming for e4-e5, after which he will get two powerful knights. The g2-pawn will not be paid any attention to.   17...hxg2  18.e5  dxe5  19.Rxd8+  Rxd8  20.Nxe5  White's pieces control all over the board and it is time to pick the low hanging fruit, such as the pawn on h6. }
