{ This is a novelty.   11.Nxb3  Bd6  0-1 @@StartBracket@@43@@EndBracket@@ Merrheim, X @@StartBracket@@2390@@EndBracket@@ -Schwarte, J @@StartBracket@@2320@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2014  12.Na5!?  This deserves a try. }
11... Nd7 12. b4
{ In this case, the doubled pawn is definitely not a weakening of the structure! The open a-file can be used for the rooks. }
12... Be7 13. d4
{ This strong and instructive move resolves the backward d3-pawn.   Black faces a difficult choice: allow the deterioration of the structure after  13...f6  14.dxe5  fxe5  ,   or allowing the knight to d4 after  13...exd4  14.Nxd4  . }
