18... h5 19. Rh1 O-O-O 20. Qf2
{ This position is so complex that the engines start doubting their own assessments, with a '0.00' evaluation. It means we are on our own; machines can no longer help us. As a matter of fact, contrary to engines' evaluation it is more important that we understand the position. After our opponent finding all these difficult moves, which was even out of bounds for Carlsen, we managed to halt the g- and h-pawns, and we are set for the advance of the a- and b-pawns. Please give me the white pieces!   20.Qf2  g3  21.Qg2  h4  22.Rh3  when Giri successfully blocked the pawns. Please cast a glance at Giri-Tari in the Model Games section for typical plans here. }
*

