{ Black will find himself down in rabbit hole, as will be shown in the next lines. }
15. Qe2
{ It doesn't seem like that this dull-looking position could disbalance our opponent in a couple of moves. In fact, this position contains prosperous attacking prospects: White is set to start an awful attack on Black.   15.a4?  We can't allow Rxd3, as will be shown in the next line.  15...Rxd3  16.a5  Bxf3  17.gxf3  Qe6  18.axb6  cxb6  19.Ne3  Ng6  is winning for Black.   19...Ng6!  20.Ng2  to stop Nh4.  20...Rhd8  21.Rb2  Qd6  White must return the piece, ending up in a hopeless situation. }
15... Ne6 { is too slow, because of } 16. a4 a6 17. b5 axb5 18. axb5 c5 19. Ra1
