{ We are renewing the threat along the g-file. The pawn push h4-h5-h6 is on the agenda. }
27... Qd6 { Black cannot stop h4-h5 by Qe8, as the knight would be hanging. }
28. h5 h6 29. Rg6 Qe7 30. Kg2 Qd6 { This weak move allows Bxh6. } 31. Bxh6 gxh6
{ Given that the c4-square is available for the queen, the sacrifice works. }
32. Qc4 { with the double attack on a2 and g8, is winning for White. } *

