8. d4
{ 8.Nbd2  O-O  9.b4  Bd6  10.Nc4  Re8!  A prophylaxis for the following knight manoeuvre...  11.Be3  This whole line looks impressive for White, grabbing the initiative on the queenside. Nonetheless, Black can launch a counterattack on the kingside, starting with the knight manoeuvre ...Nd7-f8-g6.  11...Nf8  12.h3  Ng6  13.a4  Bf8  14.Qc2  Qf6!  Black obtained here sufficient counterplay: h3 is weak and Nf4 or h4 is about to follow. ½-½ @@StartBracket@@35@@EndBracket@@ Anton Guijarro,D @@StartBracket@@2703@@EndBracket@@ -Salgado Lopez,I @@StartBracket@@2584@@EndBracket@@ chess24.com INT 2020. }
