10. Nbd2
{ In a recent game, Magnus tried here against Radjabov:  10.Re1!?  c5  11.Na3  cxd4  12.cxd4  f6  13.Bh4  Nb6  14.Bg3  Bg4  15.Qb3+  Kh8   A possible improvement could be  15...Be6  but Magnus would have maintained the pressure with  16.Qc3  when the World Champion's chances are slightly preferable.  16.Nb5⩲  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@74@@EndBracket@@ Carlsen, M @@StartBracket@@2855@@EndBracket@@ - Radjabov, T @@StartBracket@@2763@@EndBracket@@ chess24.com INT 2021 }
