11. dxe5
{ Probably the best, otherwise Black would have stabilized his center by means of ...f7-f6. }
11... Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Qxe5
{ This looks like the most natural move, but as goes more often: the most logical isn't the strongest continuation. }
13. f4 Qe8 { With a temp, White takes over in the center. } 14. e5
{ White wins time and forces to hand over one of his bishops. } 14... Be7 15.
Bxe7 Qxe7
{ Black can still stop the advance of the f4-pawn, for the time being. } 16.
Qf3 { White will proceed with Nd2-c4-e3, to lift the blockade on f5. } *

