Bf6
{ This is one of these rare occasions where Kramnik plays an inaccurate move. How should White proceed in order to obtain a solid positional plus? }
12. b4 { White gains control over the d5-square after b4-b5. } 12... Re8 13. a4
{ There was nothing wrong with  13.b5!?  cxb5  14.cxb5 } 13... Nf8
{ The knight is on its way to d4. In contrast to the d5-square, the d4-square is well protected by the e3-bishop.   13...a6  doesn't stop White from playing b4-b5:  14.b5  axb5  15.axb5  cxb5  16.cxb5± }
14. b5 Qd7 15. Rfb1 Ne6 16. bxc6 { Exchanging the defender of the d5-square. }
16... Qxc6 17. a5 a6 18. Nd5
{ White obtained a large advantage. He can follow up with Rb2 and Rab1. } *

