{ A splendid knight manoeuvre to d3. } 20... Rfd8 21. Ke2 Nf8 22. Nd3
{ Objectively, White is slightly better. Practically, he is much better because of the weak pawn structure of Black @@StartBracket@@for more comprehensive explanation about the positional aspects please check out the video@@EndBracket@@.   For example  22...Rd6  23.Ra3  Rad8  24.c4  We see that with each move our opponent's position gets more cramped.  24...Bh5+  25.f3  Ne6  26.Rc2  Nd4+  27.Bxd4  Rxd4  28.Nc5  Rb8  29.Ndb3  The c5-knight will reoccupy d3 from where it hits Black isolated pawn on e5. This ugly duckling needs constant care. The other knight can be moved to c5, tying the b8-rook. }
